tags: i just stay far away from ship wars
there are ships i like and ships i don't but i'm not gonna fight anyone about it
summary:
thefirewithallthestrengthithath
 replied to your photo  “Actress: The role I’m playing is a victim that’s being manipulated...
body:
thefirewithallthestrengthithath replied to your photo “Actress: The role I’m playing is a victim that’s being manipulated and…”
i’ll be interested to see how many current so-called fans end up turning on the series and all of its creators if kylo’s redemption and/or reylo endgame does happen in TROS…i’ve seen pettiness on both sides of this little ship war

Yeah, I’d honestly be pretty surprised if kylo doesn’t get redemption, this is Star Wars after all. I’m personally not in favour of reylo endgame but I’m watching for spaceships and lightsabers and light vs dark, not whether or not two characters get together.

title: Star Wars Tagging!
body:
So as a head’s up, these are the various Star Wars tags I’ll be using for the rest of the year:

  • star wars - Anything relating to any of the movies/cartoons/books
  • rogue one - Anything relating to that movie of the Cassian Andor spin-off
  • sw spoilers - Anything spoilery for Episode IX or the various other upcoming projects
  • anti-tlj - Anything critical of “The Last Jedi”

If you need to block any of these, please feel free! I want you to keep your dash the way you like.

summary: Maxima-A class heavy cruiser. The Maxima-A class heavy cruiser first appeared in the 2015 canon novel Before the Awakening,...
body: Maxima-A class heavy cruiser. The Maxima-A class heavy cruiser first appeared in the 2015 canon novel Before the Awakening, written by Greg Rucka.[1] The cruisers were first pictured in the 2016 comic book Poe Dameron 2: Black Squadron, Part II, written by Charles Soule and illustrated by Phil Noto.

summary: Star Wars: Daisy Ridley non apprezza l'idea della romance nota come "Reylo"
title: Star Wars: Daisy Ridley non apprezza l'idea della romance nota come "Reylo"
body:
Star Wars: Daisy Ridley non apprezza l’idea della romance nota come “Reylo”

Come sapete, ad alcune persone piace piacere l’idea di una storia d’amore tra Rey e Kylo Ren (definita Reylo) in Star Wars, ma questo a quanto pare non include l’attrice Daisy Ridley.

Durante una recente intervista alla Star Wars Celebration di quest’anno a Chicago, all’attrice è stato chiesto cosa ne pensasse di una possibile storia d’amore tra i due personaggi. Nello specifico, si riferivano…
